trans-unit.source: When a message is successfully deleted, it is immediately marked for deletion and is no longer accessible to clients.
trans-unit.target: When a message is successfully deleted, it is immediately marked for deletion and is no longer accessible to clients.

trans-unit.source: The message is later removed from the queue during garbage collection.
trans-unit.target: The message is later removed from the queue during garbage collection.

trans-unit.source: After a client retrieves a message with the <link xlink:href="d4c13c95-acaa-47ff-940e-f8038da44fad" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Get Messages</link> operation, the client is expected to process and delete the message.
trans-unit.target: After a client retrieves a message with the <link xlink:href="d4c13c95-acaa-47ff-940e-f8038da44fad" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Get Messages</link> operation, the client is expected to process and delete the message.

trans-unit.source: To delete the message, you must have two items of data returned in the response body of the <unmanagedCodeEntityReference>Get Messages</unmanagedCodeEntityReference> operation:
trans-unit.target: To delete the message, you must have two items of data returned in the response body of the <unmanagedCodeEntityReference>Get Messages</unmanagedCodeEntityReference> operation:

trans-unit.source: The message ID, an opaque GUID value that identifies the message in the queue.
trans-unit.target: The message ID, an opaque GUID value that identifies the message in the queue.

trans-unit.source: A valid pop receipt, an opaque value that indicates that the message has been retrieved.
trans-unit.target: A valid pop receipt, an opaque value that indicates that the message has been retrieved.

trans-unit.source: The message ID is returned from the previous <unmanagedCodeEntityReference>Get Messages</unmanagedCodeEntityReference> operation.
trans-unit.target: The message ID is returned from the previous <unmanagedCodeEntityReference>Get Messages</unmanagedCodeEntityReference> operation.

trans-unit.source: The pop receipt is returned from the most recent <unmanagedCodeEntityReference>Get Messages</unmanagedCodeEntityReference> or <unmanagedCodeEntityReference>Update Message</unmanagedCodeEntityReference> operation.
trans-unit.target: The pop receipt is returned from the most recent <unmanagedCodeEntityReference>Get Messages</unmanagedCodeEntityReference> or <unmanagedCodeEntityReference>Update Message</unmanagedCodeEntityReference> operation.

trans-unit.source: In order for the <unmanagedCodeEntityReference>Delete Message</unmanagedCodeEntityReference> operation to succeed, the pop receipt specified on the request must match the pop receipt returned from the <unmanagedCodeEntityReference>Get Messages</unmanagedCodeEntityReference> or <unmanagedCodeEntityReference>Update Message</unmanagedCodeEntityReference> operation.
trans-unit.target: In order for the <unmanagedCodeEntityReference>Delete Message</unmanagedCodeEntityReference> operation to succeed, the pop receipt specified on the request must match the pop receipt returned from the <unmanagedCodeEntityReference>Get Messages</unmanagedCodeEntityReference> or <unmanagedCodeEntityReference>Update Message</unmanagedCodeEntityReference> operation.

trans-unit.source: Pop receipts remain valid until one of the following events occurs:
trans-unit.target: Pop receipts remain valid until one of the following events occurs:

trans-unit.source: The message has expired.
trans-unit.target: The message has expired.

trans-unit.source: The message has been deleted using the last pop receipt received either from <languageKeyword>Get Messages</languageKeyword> or <languageKeyword>Update Message</languageKeyword>.
trans-unit.target: The message has been deleted using the last pop receipt received either from <languageKeyword>Get Messages</languageKeyword> or <languageKeyword>Update Message</languageKeyword>.

trans-unit.source: The invisibility timeout has elapsed and the message has been dequeued by a <languageKeyword>Get Messages</languageKeyword> request.
trans-unit.target: The invisibility timeout has elapsed and the message has been dequeued by a <languageKeyword>Get Messages</languageKeyword> request.

trans-unit.source: When the invisibility timeout elapses, the message becomes visible again.
trans-unit.target: When the invisibility timeout elapses, the message becomes visible again.

trans-unit.source: If it is retrieved by another <languageKeyword>Get Messages</languageKeyword> request, the returned pop receipt can be used to delete or update the message.
trans-unit.target: If it is retrieved by another <languageKeyword>Get Messages</languageKeyword> request, the returned pop receipt can be used to delete or update the message.

trans-unit.source: The message has been updated with a new visibility timeout.
trans-unit.target: The message has been updated with a new visibility timeout.

trans-unit.source: When the message is updated, a new pop receipt will be returned.
trans-unit.target: When the message is updated, a new pop receipt will be returned.

trans-unit.source: If a message with a matching pop receipt is not found, the service returns error code 404 (Not Found).
trans-unit.target: If a message with a matching pop receipt is not found, the service returns error code 404 (Not Found).

trans-unit.source: This error will happen in the cases listed above where the pop receipt is no longer valid.
trans-unit.target: This error will happen in the cases listed above where the pop receipt is no longer valid.
